                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi all.  Been browsing these boards for a while for the great tips and general all-around awesomeness, but this is my first time actually posting.  I registered and even took a shot at making my own enchanter code.
<br />

<br />
I was hoping some of the enchanters here had advice on how I might safely charm in the mountain trials.  Groups always ask me to charm there, and while I do enjoy charming, the prospect of a bad break and subsequent wipe and failure is daunting (dead cleric = no rezzer = start from beginning), since I'm currently still trying to be KT flagged.
<br />

<br />
I have 2.3k HP (around 4.1k-4.7k HP when group buffed), gear is extremely average, mostly bazaar stuff.  With arcane rune, uproar and LR5, I find that being hit on a break can take me down to 50% near instantly, so I have really little room for error.
<br />

<br />
So far I've tried two methods of handling the breaks:
<br />

<br />
1. With a trials group that had no snarer but was heavy on the stuns/mezzes, I made a hotkey screaming bloody murder, and would pray someone's stun or mez would take hold before I died.  This necessitated me tanking as I tried to channel my own stun, and I could be at anything from 40-60% when the pet was back under control.   Amazingly I never died, but it always seemed risky.
<br />

<br />
2. Snares, and hopefully even sinia.  Snared and maloed, the pet was of course, easy to control in itself, but I found other problems cropping up.  I tried to keep it a safe distance from me so I would never get hit, but if I left it too far behind the group, it would aggro respawns/roamers.  If I left the pet with the group while I stayed behind, I would aggro respawns/roamers (in one tipt group, the respawn or wanderer offed me from behind with lightning speed, and the pet and add then proceeded to chew the cleric up).  Yet another time, our monk pulled 2, and I ran a little closer to mez, putting me in melee range of pet, which promptly chose to break charm and send me back to bind.  
<br />

<br />
I'm definitely gonna keep trying till I get it right, but I'm starting to feel dismayed at being such a sucky chanter.  How does everyone else control their 1k-hitting pet safely?  What am I missing here?
<br />

<br />
And in that vein, is it possible to haste and DW the pet without increasing the risk of dying?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />E65.161/MS h+ 2.3khp 4km ft10 !G e++@ o--- T+++++ L+ H++(--) f+++ !g(+)@ b- c++ t++ D--- !X(+)@</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
