                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Aye, a snarer is key, they reduce your risk factor tremendously.  You're on the right track when using snare as control.. stay back away from your pet. 
<br />
 
<br />
It takes a little practice but eventually you get a feel for how far back you can be w/o worrying about agro'ing back pops.. also with Pooka DPS your group should be moving forward fast enough that you should be well ahead of back pops.  Have SoE (or equiv) up at all times and stay high on the walls. Vertical distance is more time time it takes for your ex-pet to reach you and less distance you have to be from your group. 
<br />
 
<br />
Most Vxed/Tipt groups are going to have a cleric. Use your panic button (CHARM BREAK! RE-SNARE and STUN PLEASE!) and teach your cleric to stun on breaks.  I recommend against trying to use WoM or Color Cloud to control the pet.. these put you way too close to a pet that when properly hasted and dual wielding can 1 round you. 
<br />
 
<br />
Once you get the feel for it, you'll find yourself volunteering to help others through the trials just because they are fun.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
