                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Snare is good.  I would also avoid using standard pet control.  WoM and CC are great when you can get them off without fear of instant death, but that's not really the case with the Pookie.
<br />

<br />
Also, if your group really wants you to charm something that powerful they will have to be aware of the danger and the help you'll need.  Hotkeys work, but don't be afraid to take that extra step prior to forming the group to make sure that you have a snarer.  If you can't get a snarer, get a wizzie or a pally that can stun.  Personally, I like a druid as a support class.  They are so versatile.  They are decent nuke DPS with some decent DoTs, they can snare, backup heal, and in a pinch they can Succor.  Hopefully the group will understand; a loose Pookie might as well proc an unresistable AE death touch if it manages to kill the chanter.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" />
