                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was in a very interesting Pooka group once.  We had 2 chanters (me + 1) and you can guess who was doing all the DPS...  The great thing was, we staggered the charms so that we had two pookas going and breaks wouldnt happen at the same time (usually).  We recharmed regularly outside of pulls to keep breaks at a min.  When her pooka broke, I mezzed and she did the rest.  When mine broke, we reversed it.  What ended up making the adv difficult was the snarer...  I couldnt get them to announce thier snares and on at least two breaks we had a wild unsnared pooka that nearly took us out.  Didnt quite make the target as a few bailed before the end (hate it when that happens!).
<br />

<br />
Things I will insist on to do "The Pooka"
<br />

<br />
1)  Any Snarer.
<br />
2)  A Cleric.
<br />
3)  A Mage.
<br />
4)  A good puller.
<br />

<br />
Everything else is gravy.  Ok, maybe the mage is a bit optional, but I wont even attempt without the other three.
<br />

<br />
Enkidoo
<br />
Proud Merchant of the 65th Order of KEI</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
