                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personally like a bard, makes a great puller and a nice back up mezzer.  My guild has some very talented bards, which make me feel very comfortable charming in groups.
<br />

<br />
Hotkey in group can make everyone aware of break, if you have two healers you can have Cleric stun the mob on break. If you have a pally can have them stun if they aren't Main Tank.
<br />

<br />
Pooka's are best done with snare I suppose but I have successfully done them without snare several times, key for me is Word of Morrell and Mez Mastery.  Gives you time to tash and recharm.
<br />

<br />
Course here is where I weigh in heavy on Charisma vs HP debate.  I would agree that Charisma helps in charming, but that the charm is going to break eventually, when it does the, the more HP and defensive abilities that a chanter has the longer the healer(s) and support classes have time to help you out. Heck tanks can switch targets and taunt for just that momen of extra time.
<br />

<br />
If your just starting out don't be afraid to slow your pet before charming, the dps will be drastically lowered but will still be far more DPS then without a Pooka.
<br />

<br />
Testing enchanter code.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />66.444/Pr h-- 5.1Khp 6.5Km FT15 G++++! E+++++ T++ L+ F B C++++ T++++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
