                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Don't forget Paladins and SKs. I prefer paladins over SKs because their stuns are high aggro in addition to stopping the charm fodder from hitting you. I would always have my pet "guard here" wherever the current mob was being fought and sit as far away as I safely could. When charm broke, I had a hotkey that told my group charm was off and made me stand. As my pet came for me, I cast Tash, then I would run in a circle until the paladin had aggro when I would recharm. Most of the night, my pet never even broke through my arcane rune because the pally was fast on stuns. The mobs were dying so fast, I didn't slow them, I only mezzed adds.
<br />
One group I was in had 2 clerics, warrior (puller), paladin, wizard, and myself. It was just about the safest charm group I've ever been in despite a 1200 hitting pet with SoV and NDT. We even managed to survive a charm break on a 3 pull, although we lost the wizard on that pull.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51669" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sumiko Nomonashi</a>
