                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Keeping debuffs on the pet are key - tash and malosani keep the MR WAY WAY down, and help keep your durations up.  Snare is almost a must here too, just make sure its a NON DAMAGING ONE (got spanked once because I didn't make that clear).
<br />

<br />
Couple other things:
<br />

<br />
1.  ER4 item helps lots - you can run off and get range to re-charm/root or mez pet if need be.
<br />

<br />
2.  If pet is snared, after /pet guard it will stop wherever it finished the last fight - won't path back to original spot.
<br />

<br />
3.  Watchout for the stonemite acid dot - last 15 mins and I have yet to see anything take it off.  Pet is unmezzable during this time, making things a bit more exciting.
<br />

<br />
 4.  Pooks dual wield, so give em 2 weapons.  They do very nice DPS with both equipped.  Speeding them is optional, makes for HUGE increase in DPS, but... wild hasted dual wielding pet can rip folks up FAST.
<br />

<br />
5.  Pallies are really nice for stunning during breaks, also for backup rezzes if the cleric goes boom.
<br />

<br />
6.  Debuff pet regularily - don't wait for them to drop, cuz it will happen at the worst possible time.  Use a clicky invis or dispell to take off charm and haste, then mez, tash and have others malo/snare.
<br />

<br />

