                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Frequently, I do not have a snarer available when I do a tipt group.  I always fully buff my pooka.
<br />

<br />
If you stand far enough away, and you have spell haste up (ie. cleric buff + spell haste item), you should be fine to mez them or root them before they reach you.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I prefer the mez route, and the few times when a Noc has actually dot'd my pet, I end up rooting it, and having the cleric cure the dot so I can mez later.  Since the Noc's are not all that prevalent, you need not worry about that dot too much... its a killer, though if you don't pay attention and expect it to take hold.  I rarely have difficulty controling the pooka.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=406237" target="_blank" class="postlink">Baalazai</a>
<br />
Rodcet Nife
<br />
<a href="http://www.echoesineternity.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Echoes in Eternity</a>
