                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If I understand slow mitigation properly, using Tepid Deeds is much better in GoD trials than Forlorn Deeds.  Tepid is 50%, it costs less and it's got a 3.5 second cast time (2.9 with Bone Sliver Ornament).  I always use it there and just about anywhere that slow is mitigated (high end PoP), and have never had any issues of it being too weak of a slow.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=515779" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://lunapark.org/~luna/mithrasig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
