                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In my opinion, charming should be as inobtrusive to the group as possible. When I'm charming pets in tipt, I rarely haste it. The thing is that with MM, max defensive AAs and runes up, I can do 90% of all recharms by just WoM, retash, recharm, and take little to no damage, as long as it is not hasted. I never run, the pet is back in action only 12 secs after breaking, and only my healer has to be slightly observant of what is going on. 
<br />

<br />
Others can do what they do best, and not feel continously edgy about the pet. Snares are ok, but not really needed. Malo and debuffs are cool, if the caster gets it in between breaks once in a while. I never make "OMG-BREAK-..." hotkeys since I feel they cause more harm than good. In general I think there are too many downsides in hasting pets in tipt. You get faster kill speed, but not really all that much, concidering that alot (sometimes most) of the time is "downtime" being spent by pulling or whatever. And if you are rooting or mezing on breaks, your pet will be out of action so much, that you really arent getting much out of the added haste. Certainly not enough to offset the added risk imo. Even running around or lagging behind the group is too obtrusive to me concidering that the group often needs me in the front line to mez, and sometimes to slow.
<br />

<br />
I havent died to my pooka yet.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
